1
00:01:26,640 --> 00:01:34,960
[LIVE UP TO YOUR YOUTH]

2
00:01:35,600 --> 00:01:37,680
[Episode 6]

3
00:01:41,789 --> 00:01:43,590
Have you seen the mother and son?

4
00:01:45,680 --> 00:01:46,940
Did Chen Yan ask you...

5
00:01:47,090 --> 00:01:48,620
to pass on any message to me?

6
00:01:52,800 --> 00:01:53,660
No, she didn't.

7
00:01:56,590 --> 00:01:57,850
Tie, I'm here this time

8
00:01:58,600 --> 00:02:00,390
for my own business.

9
00:02:01,810 --> 00:02:03,940
I'm staying at Seasons Change Hostel.

10
00:02:08,860 --> 00:02:09,910
Oh, that matter!

11
00:02:11,860 --> 00:02:12,350
Yo, Bro.

12
00:02:12,780 --> 00:02:14,130
That was what you wanted to talk about?

13
00:02:14,130 --> 00:02:15,180
You making such a big deal out of it

14
00:02:15,180 --> 00:02:16,150
scared me.

15
00:02:19,079 --> 00:02:20,780
You're staying
at Seasons Change Hostel too?

16
00:02:20,780 --> 00:02:21,420
Yeah.

17
00:02:21,910 --> 00:02:22,610
Bro, I...

18
00:02:22,680 --> 00:02:24,020
I just arrived in Beijing.

19
00:02:24,020 --> 00:02:24,690
Seasons Change Hostel

20
00:02:24,690 --> 00:02:26,420
was the first place I stayed at.

21
00:02:26,530 --> 00:02:28,329
I treat it like home,

22
00:02:28,590 --> 00:02:29,720
and the people there

23
00:02:29,800 --> 00:02:30,860
are like my family.

24
00:02:30,910 --> 00:02:32,400
Many of them have already paid

25
00:02:32,400 --> 00:02:33,960
several months of rent.

26
00:02:34,340 --> 00:02:36,130
Kicking them out now

27
00:02:36,130 --> 00:02:37,410
wouldn't be right.

28
00:02:37,520 --> 00:02:38,590
It has to be first come, first served.

29
00:02:38,590 --> 00:02:40,390
We have to be reasonable, right?

30
00:02:44,030 --> 00:02:44,760
Reasonable?

31
00:02:47,020 --> 00:02:48,610
I'm not capable of that.

32
00:02:51,500 --> 00:02:52,100
Young man,

33
00:02:52,520 --> 00:02:54,960
you're much better than those three.

34
00:02:55,650 --> 00:02:57,579
They were just straight-up lying.

35
00:02:58,400 --> 00:02:59,600
You came to talk to me,

36
00:02:59,870 --> 00:03:00,690
all straightforward.

37
00:03:00,690 --> 00:03:02,090
I like your personality.

38
00:03:02,840 --> 00:03:04,370
What? Are you their boss?

39
00:03:04,430 --> 00:03:04,960
No.

40
00:03:05,780 --> 00:03:07,600
There's no such thing

41
00:03:07,740 --> 00:03:08,250
there.

42
00:03:08,900 --> 00:03:10,560
We come from all over the country.

43
00:03:10,560 --> 00:03:12,490
We're all here to chase our dreams.

44
00:03:12,520 --> 00:03:13,020
Dreams!

45
00:03:15,370 --> 00:03:16,550
We're unlike you.

46
00:03:17,190 --> 00:03:18,740
When you first came to Beijing,

47
00:03:18,740 --> 00:03:20,070
you had so much capital.

48
00:03:25,180 --> 00:03:26,579
You're close to Chen Yan.

49
00:03:27,650 --> 00:03:29,079
I'm doing this for her sake.

50
00:03:29,079 --> 00:03:29,740
How's that?

51
00:03:30,079 --> 00:03:31,520
If you want to eat here,

52
00:03:32,180 --> 00:03:32,960
then stay.

53
00:03:33,780 --> 00:03:34,750
If you don't,

54
00:03:35,530 --> 00:03:36,079
get out.

55
00:03:40,560 --> 00:03:41,910
Get lost.

56
00:03:41,930 --> 00:03:43,190
Don't you understand?

57
00:03:43,210 --> 00:03:43,780
Get lost!

58
00:03:44,030 --> 00:03:45,180
-Don't touch me.
-Go. Get out.

59
00:03:45,180 --> 00:03:45,960
Don't touch me.

60
00:03:45,960 --> 00:03:46,860
-Get out!
-Don't touch me.

61
00:03:46,860 --> 00:03:47,870
Let me say one last thing!

62
00:03:47,870 --> 00:03:49,000
You talk too much.

63
00:03:50,410 --> 00:03:52,030
This is for your ears only.

64
00:03:53,710 --> 00:03:54,650
Come, come.

65
00:03:54,650 --> 00:03:55,070
Speak!

66
00:03:55,620 --> 00:03:56,310
Let go.

67
00:04:10,240 --> 00:04:12,280
When Chen Yan was pregnant,

68
00:04:13,120 --> 00:04:15,150
you made money
through ways you shouldn't have.

69
00:04:15,150 --> 00:04:17,250
That guy is still looking for you.

70
00:04:30,830 --> 00:04:32,159
What are you looking at?

71
00:04:32,420 --> 00:04:33,680
You don't know who I am?

72
00:04:43,440 --> 00:04:45,050
You dared to come to me alone.

73
00:04:45,750 --> 00:04:47,350
I respect you for being a man.

74
00:04:49,750 --> 00:04:51,770
But as for the Seasons Change Hostel—

75
00:04:51,770 --> 00:04:53,170
I will go, no matter what.

76
00:04:57,870 --> 00:04:58,720
I'll go with you.

77
00:04:58,720 --> 00:04:59,920
No need. You guys eat.

78
00:05:10,450 --> 00:05:12,180
If I don't settle this today,

79
00:05:12,980 --> 00:05:14,310
I'm going to Wenzhou!

80
00:05:23,030 --> 00:05:25,290
Fine! I'll send you to Wenzhou right now!

81
00:05:31,630 --> 00:05:32,130
Come on!

82
00:05:32,570 --> 00:05:33,500
Really leaving?

83
00:05:33,830 --> 00:05:34,270
I'm leaving.

84
00:05:34,270 --> 00:05:34,800
Bye, Luo.

85
00:05:34,800 --> 00:05:36,010
-Take care.
-You've got everything.

86
00:05:36,010 --> 00:05:36,640
Got it all.

87
00:05:36,670 --> 00:05:37,470
Take care.

88
00:05:37,600 --> 00:05:38,220
Bye, Luo.

89
00:05:41,750 --> 00:05:42,750
Everyone's gone.

90
00:05:43,240 --> 00:05:44,300
It's just us left.

91
00:05:46,159 --> 00:05:46,770
In the end,

92
00:05:46,770 --> 00:05:48,000
it's just us left.

93
00:05:49,470 --> 00:05:51,400
All good things must come to an end.

94
00:05:51,740 --> 00:05:52,750
I advise you guys

95
00:05:53,360 --> 00:05:54,890
to find a new place quickly.

96
00:05:55,870 --> 00:05:56,560
If you ever

97
00:05:56,560 --> 00:05:58,000
miss me, Little Northeasterner,

98
00:05:58,000 --> 00:05:59,130
come back and see me.

99
00:05:59,220 --> 00:06:00,750
As long as the Seasons Change Hostel's sign

100
00:06:00,750 --> 00:06:01,550
is still here,

101
00:06:01,720 --> 00:06:02,570
I, Little Northeasterner,

102
00:06:02,570 --> 00:06:04,930
will still be right here
waiting for everyone.

103
00:06:04,930 --> 00:06:05,660
Liangliang.

104
00:06:06,180 --> 00:06:07,640
Have you found a place yet?

105
00:06:07,920 --> 00:06:08,460
No.

106
00:06:09,010 --> 00:06:10,660
There's a place that's free.

107
00:06:12,300 --> 00:06:12,860
Free?

108
00:06:13,000 --> 00:06:14,450
Have you seen Mr. Xu?

109
00:06:16,920 --> 00:06:17,890
Probably ran away.

110
00:06:17,890 --> 00:06:19,730
He wouldn't run even if you did.

111
00:06:20,000 --> 00:06:21,660
His stuff is still in the room.

112
00:06:21,770 --> 00:06:22,390
He probably

113
00:06:22,390 --> 00:06:23,980
just didn't have time to pack.

114
00:06:23,980 --> 00:06:26,180
He probably fled in panic.

115
00:06:30,060 --> 00:06:30,990
Where is Ranran?

116
00:06:32,650 --> 00:06:33,710
Crying in the room.

117
00:06:33,800 --> 00:06:34,800
Why is she crying?

118
00:06:36,740 --> 00:06:37,430
I need to go check on her.

119
00:06:37,430 --> 00:06:38,230
Go have a look.

120
00:06:41,450 --> 00:06:45,250
Today, we drink the celebration wine.

121
00:06:46,560 --> 00:06:50,240
I vow never to rest until my goal is met.

122
00:06:50,240 --> 00:06:54,620
The future is long for us
to show our skills.

123
00:06:56,040 --> 00:06:57,250
Willing—

124
00:07:02,270 --> 00:07:03,400
Where is Xu Shengli?

125
00:07:04,620 --> 00:07:05,710
Feng Tieyou.

126
00:07:05,810 --> 00:07:07,350
Didn't we have a deal?

127
00:07:07,830 --> 00:07:08,890
For the remaining tenants,

128
00:07:08,890 --> 00:07:09,930
give them a few more days.

129
00:07:09,930 --> 00:07:10,450
Once they find a place,

130
00:07:10,450 --> 00:07:11,450
they'll move out.

131
00:07:11,830 --> 00:07:12,960
You promised me too.

132
00:07:13,300 --> 00:07:14,250
Why are you here again?

133
00:07:14,250 --> 00:07:15,670
Is there no end to this?

134
00:07:15,720 --> 00:07:16,190
It's the middle of the night.

135
00:07:16,190 --> 00:07:17,720
What act are you putting on?

136
00:07:19,040 --> 00:07:20,160
Stop wasting your breath.

137
00:07:20,160 --> 00:07:21,290
Where is Xu Shengli?

138
00:07:26,720 --> 00:07:27,580
You don't know?

139
00:07:29,950 --> 00:07:30,760
I do.

140
00:07:35,220 --> 00:07:36,070
Xu Shengli!

141
00:07:37,360 --> 00:07:39,230
Xu Shengli!

142
00:07:41,330 --> 00:07:42,900
Xu Shengli!

143
00:07:46,300 --> 00:07:47,180
Xu Shengli.

144
00:07:48,010 --> 00:07:48,930
From today on,

145
00:07:48,930 --> 00:07:50,210
Xu Shengli is my bro!

146
00:07:51,300 --> 00:07:53,850
I really didn't scare you today.

147
00:07:54,000 --> 00:07:55,180
If he had died today,

148
00:07:55,190 --> 00:07:56,680
I would have had to pay with my life.

149
00:07:56,680 --> 00:07:57,890
If he had been crippled,

150
00:07:57,890 --> 00:07:59,690
I would have been sentenced too!

151
00:07:59,920 --> 00:08:01,180
What's the date today?

152
00:08:01,190 --> 00:08:02,000
Doesn't matter.

153
00:08:02,000 --> 00:08:03,110
This day next year

154
00:08:03,180 --> 00:08:04,680
will be the death anniversary
for us brothers.

155
00:08:04,680 --> 00:08:05,280
No, no, no.

156
00:08:05,430 --> 00:08:06,600
What death anniversary?

157
00:08:06,600 --> 00:08:07,600
Oh, no, I misspoke.

158
00:08:07,600 --> 00:08:09,270
It'd be our anniversary.

159
00:08:11,420 --> 00:08:12,360
What's going on?

160
00:08:14,450 --> 00:08:14,980
No big deal.

161
00:08:14,980 --> 00:08:15,420
Well,

162
00:08:15,450 --> 00:08:17,630
you are all his...

163
00:08:18,000 --> 00:08:18,930
buddies, right?

164
00:08:21,300 --> 00:08:22,760
There's a pretty lady here too.

165
00:08:22,760 --> 00:08:23,430
Sis.

166
00:08:23,690 --> 00:08:24,450
Actually,

167
00:08:24,450 --> 00:08:26,180
Officer Tang from the police station

168
00:08:26,180 --> 00:08:27,170
talked to me too.

169
00:08:27,240 --> 00:08:28,610
Starting today, you

170
00:08:28,680 --> 00:08:29,450
don't have to leave.

171
00:08:29,450 --> 00:08:30,980
Just stay here and make art.

172
00:08:31,600 --> 00:08:32,110
Well,

173
00:08:32,110 --> 00:08:32,720
Little Northeasterner,

174
00:08:32,720 --> 00:08:33,429
lately,

175
00:08:33,530 --> 00:08:35,130
I've made a real mess of things for you.

176
00:08:35,130 --> 00:08:35,750
I'm sorry.

177
00:08:35,860 --> 00:08:36,559
Okay?

178
00:08:36,840 --> 00:08:38,030
Let's forget the past!

179
00:08:38,030 --> 00:08:39,500
We'll wipe the slate clean today.

180
00:08:39,500 --> 00:08:41,030
Let's start fresh tomorrow.

181
00:08:41,030 --> 00:08:42,320
You guys are my bros,

182
00:08:42,440 --> 00:08:42,900
and sis.

183
00:08:42,960 --> 00:08:43,549
Okay?

184
00:08:43,580 --> 00:08:44,710
The power is back on.

185
00:08:45,600 --> 00:08:46,210
Sorry.

186
00:08:46,410 --> 00:08:47,540
The water situation

187
00:08:48,100 --> 00:08:49,390
has nothing to do with me.

188
00:08:49,390 --> 00:08:49,820
Sorry.

189
00:08:50,130 --> 00:08:51,130
I'm really sorry.

190
00:08:51,270 --> 00:08:52,440
Just make do for one more night,

191
00:08:52,440 --> 00:08:52,890
okay?

192
00:08:53,030 --> 00:08:54,630
Then how do I take a shower...

193
00:08:57,120 --> 00:08:58,160
That's that, Shengli.

194
00:08:58,160 --> 00:08:59,670
I don't know if I made myself clear.

195
00:08:59,670 --> 00:09:00,390
You made yourself clear!

196
00:09:00,390 --> 00:09:00,870
I did?

197
00:09:00,870 --> 00:09:01,320
Bro.

198
00:09:03,200 --> 00:09:04,100
From now on,

199
00:09:04,370 --> 00:09:05,370
this is your home.

200
00:09:05,480 --> 00:09:06,670
You're always welcome

201
00:09:06,670 --> 00:09:07,910
at Seasons Change Hostel.

202
00:09:07,910 --> 00:09:08,640
Am I?

203
00:09:08,670 --> 00:09:09,790
Of course!

204
00:09:10,980 --> 00:09:11,320
Okay!

205
00:09:11,840 --> 00:09:12,650
That's great!

206
00:09:14,840 --> 00:09:15,970
Section Chief Wang!

207
00:09:21,580 --> 00:09:22,250
Sis.

208
00:09:22,290 --> 00:09:24,150
Just think of me as a crazy person.

209
00:09:24,940 --> 00:09:26,000
All right, I'm leaving.

210
00:09:26,000 --> 00:09:26,630
I'm off.

211
00:09:27,530 --> 00:09:28,410
We're all family now.

212
00:09:28,410 --> 00:09:29,390
Stay here tonight.

213
00:09:29,390 --> 00:09:30,620
Let's have a drink together.

214
00:09:30,620 --> 00:09:31,290
Stay here?

215
00:09:32,650 --> 00:09:34,000
No, he meant...

216
00:09:34,120 --> 00:09:35,010
M-Maybe not today.

217
00:09:35,010 --> 00:09:36,410
Let's drink another day.

218
00:09:39,120 --> 00:09:39,780
Walk me out.

219
00:09:40,250 --> 00:09:40,870
Well...

220
00:09:41,270 --> 00:09:41,910
Shengli.

221
00:09:42,650 --> 00:09:43,780
Making it in Beijing

222
00:09:43,840 --> 00:09:44,510
isn't easy.

223
00:09:45,010 --> 00:09:46,870
You're here to chase your dreams.

224
00:09:47,480 --> 00:09:48,290
Well,

225
00:09:48,960 --> 00:09:49,410
if...

226
00:09:51,030 --> 00:09:52,220
if anyone bullies you,

227
00:09:52,220 --> 00:09:52,950
just tell me.

228
00:09:53,460 --> 00:09:53,870
Okay.

229
00:09:55,770 --> 00:09:57,050
I shouldn't be telling you this.

230
00:09:57,050 --> 00:09:57,910
All these years

231
00:09:58,720 --> 00:10:00,780
Chen Yan and I have been divorced for,

232
00:10:01,320 --> 00:10:03,050
she wouldn't let me see the kid.

233
00:10:04,150 --> 00:10:05,990
And I still miss the kid.

234
00:10:10,030 --> 00:10:12,150
We just have different personalities.

235
00:10:12,150 --> 00:10:13,370
We fight every time we meet.

236
00:10:13,370 --> 00:10:14,440
Every single time.

237
00:10:15,000 --> 00:10:16,730
She wouldn't let me see the kid.

238
00:10:18,030 --> 00:10:20,490
You two just have different personalities.

239
00:10:22,510 --> 00:10:22,940
Bro,

240
00:10:24,010 --> 00:10:25,580
I... I'm young.

241
00:10:25,820 --> 00:10:27,550
I might be speaking out of turn.

242
00:10:28,620 --> 00:10:29,890
But I think

243
00:10:29,890 --> 00:10:31,750
what Chen Yan needs most right now

244
00:10:34,270 --> 00:10:35,410
is a good husband.

245
00:10:36,500 --> 00:10:37,960
And what the kid needs most

246
00:10:40,660 --> 00:10:41,720
is a good father.

247
00:10:43,650 --> 00:10:44,750
I can help you.

248
00:10:44,750 --> 00:10:45,800
I can.

249
00:10:48,130 --> 00:10:49,260
But for this matter,

250
00:10:50,750 --> 00:10:52,210
you have to do it yourself.

251
00:10:56,550 --> 00:10:58,460
I'm learning things from you instead.

252
00:10:58,460 --> 00:10:59,610
No, no.

253
00:10:59,740 --> 00:11:01,030
I'm nobody.

254
00:11:01,620 --> 00:11:03,020
But I think you're right.

255
00:11:06,150 --> 00:11:06,680
Shengli.

256
00:11:07,960 --> 00:11:09,140
You'll definitely

257
00:11:09,580 --> 00:11:11,120
become a great screenwriter.

258
00:11:11,120 --> 00:11:12,180
I have faith in you!

259
00:11:14,150 --> 00:11:14,610
Really?

260
00:11:14,890 --> 00:11:15,500
Really!

261
00:11:21,220 --> 00:11:23,410
A great screenwriter.

262
00:11:25,050 --> 00:11:25,720
Shengli.

263
00:11:27,790 --> 00:11:29,160
Slow down, slow down.

264
00:11:30,010 --> 00:11:31,820
What's going on?

265
00:11:36,720 --> 00:11:37,500
That's how

266
00:11:38,580 --> 00:11:39,640
the script went...

267
00:11:46,820 --> 00:11:48,220
I'll give you one more chance.

268
00:11:48,220 --> 00:11:49,480
Are you going to dodge?

269
00:11:50,580 --> 00:11:51,320
Come on!

270
00:12:12,300 --> 00:12:13,300
What's your name?

271
00:12:13,860 --> 00:12:14,710
Xu Shengli.

272
00:12:23,800 --> 00:12:25,790
A humble meal—
just a small token of respect.

273
00:12:25,790 --> 00:12:26,540
If it weren't

274
00:12:26,650 --> 00:12:28,010
for Xu this time,

275
00:12:28,320 --> 00:12:30,770
my little Seasons Change Hostel

276
00:12:30,840 --> 00:12:32,310
wouldn't have survived to the next season.

277
00:12:32,310 --> 00:12:33,140
Thank you, Xu.

278
00:12:33,530 --> 00:12:33,960
Xu,

279
00:12:34,550 --> 00:12:36,410
I'd like to propose a toast to you.

280
00:12:37,080 --> 00:12:37,540
Come on.

281
00:12:37,590 --> 00:12:39,320
We'll drink three to one glass.

282
00:12:39,360 --> 00:12:39,870
Come on.

283
00:12:39,870 --> 00:12:41,050
I-I'll finish mine.

284
00:12:41,050 --> 00:12:41,700
Come on.

285
00:12:41,700 --> 00:12:43,030
Then I'll finish mine too.

286
00:12:43,030 --> 00:12:44,820
Come on.

287
00:12:45,460 --> 00:12:46,210
Thank you.

288
00:12:50,580 --> 00:12:51,310
Refreshing!

289
00:12:52,050 --> 00:12:53,500
It's nothing.

290
00:12:53,500 --> 00:12:54,800
We have a long future ahead of us.

291
00:12:54,800 --> 00:12:55,370
Right.

292
00:12:55,700 --> 00:12:57,080
There's a long future ahead.

293
00:12:57,080 --> 00:12:58,590
This time, we can say

294
00:12:58,670 --> 00:12:59,890
we faced a disaster together.

295
00:12:59,890 --> 00:13:01,220
I saw that everyone here

296
00:13:01,600 --> 00:13:02,620
has such backbone

297
00:13:02,940 --> 00:13:04,000
and such courage.

298
00:13:04,200 --> 00:13:05,330
You are all real men.

299
00:13:05,580 --> 00:13:07,510
To be honest, the anger I had before

300
00:13:07,510 --> 00:13:08,710
has pretty much dissipated.

301
00:13:08,710 --> 00:13:09,670
Still angry, huh?

302
00:13:09,670 --> 00:13:10,360
No, no. No anger.

303
00:13:10,360 --> 00:13:11,400
It's gone now.

304
00:13:11,940 --> 00:13:12,670
We all

305
00:13:12,670 --> 00:13:15,130
come from
different corners of the country.

306
00:13:15,410 --> 00:13:16,940
We all have our own character

307
00:13:16,940 --> 00:13:18,150
and our own temper.

308
00:13:18,290 --> 00:13:18,600
Right.

309
00:13:18,600 --> 00:13:20,100
We didn't know each other before,

310
00:13:20,100 --> 00:13:22,430
so a little friction is perfectly normal.

311
00:13:22,440 --> 00:13:23,070
But,

312
00:13:24,030 --> 00:13:26,260
there's always a way to solve it.

313
00:13:26,460 --> 00:13:27,920
Like my sleeping habits—

314
00:13:28,020 --> 00:13:29,390
snoring and grinding my teeth.

315
00:13:29,390 --> 00:13:29,960
I asked!

316
00:13:30,030 --> 00:13:30,790
I asked the doctor!

317
00:13:30,790 --> 00:13:31,910
The doctor said it can be cured.

318
00:13:31,910 --> 00:13:32,470
-Really?
-Really?

319
00:13:32,470 --> 00:13:33,700
Anyway, in a nutshell,

320
00:13:33,700 --> 00:13:34,940
what happened in the past

321
00:13:34,940 --> 00:13:35,740
is in the past.

322
00:13:35,860 --> 00:13:36,520
From now on,

323
00:13:37,150 --> 00:13:38,120
let's be close—

324
00:13:38,270 --> 00:13:38,930
real close.

325
00:13:39,100 --> 00:13:39,450
Yes.

326
00:13:39,480 --> 00:13:40,780
Let's treat each other like family.

327
00:13:40,780 --> 00:13:41,410
Yes, yes.

328
00:13:41,410 --> 00:13:42,390
Xu, say no more.

329
00:13:42,410 --> 00:13:43,980
After this, we move on.

330
00:13:44,000 --> 00:13:44,700
-Let's move on.
-Let's move on.

331
00:13:44,700 --> 00:13:46,050
-Let's move on.
-Let's move on. Come on!

332
00:13:46,050 --> 00:13:47,050
Come on, drink up.

333
00:13:47,050 --> 00:13:47,750
Don't down it.

334
00:13:47,750 --> 00:13:48,670
Take it slow.

335
00:13:48,700 --> 00:13:49,670
So lively here.

336
00:13:50,820 --> 00:13:52,150
Started drinking without waiting for us?

337
00:13:52,150 --> 00:13:53,980
We went to your room,
but no one was there.

338
00:13:53,980 --> 00:13:54,570
Come on.

339
00:13:54,600 --> 00:13:55,200
Come on.

340
00:13:55,770 --> 00:13:57,650
Adding a dish for our hero here.

341
00:13:58,630 --> 00:13:59,390
Thanks.

342
00:13:59,390 --> 00:14:00,530
This glass hasn't been used.

343
00:14:00,530 --> 00:14:00,860
Okay.

344
00:14:00,860 --> 00:14:01,880
-Chopsticks. Chopsticks.
-Sit down.

345
00:14:01,880 --> 00:14:03,310
What a beautiful sight.

346
00:14:03,360 --> 00:14:04,080
You two sit next to each other.

347
00:14:04,080 --> 00:14:04,960
-Come on.
-Come on.

348
00:14:04,960 --> 00:14:05,480
Here.

349
00:14:05,600 --> 00:14:07,130
I hope I'm not interrupting.

350
00:14:07,130 --> 00:14:08,150
-No.
-No.

351
00:14:08,480 --> 00:14:10,410
We were going to invite you anyway.

352
00:14:10,820 --> 00:14:12,220
Wh-Why am I sitting here?

353
00:14:12,340 --> 00:14:13,080
Move over!

354
00:14:13,410 --> 00:14:14,440
No need!

355
00:14:14,440 --> 00:14:16,030
Just move.

356
00:14:16,480 --> 00:14:17,610
My back is acting up.

357
00:14:18,460 --> 00:14:18,940
All right.

358
00:14:18,940 --> 00:14:20,000
You sure are sharp.

359
00:14:20,750 --> 00:14:22,510
You really weren't scared yesterday?

360
00:14:22,510 --> 00:14:23,340
Those guys looked like

361
00:14:23,340 --> 00:14:24,600
they don't fear death.

362
00:14:24,960 --> 00:14:27,170
I didn't even think about being scared.

363
00:14:27,240 --> 00:14:28,270
I was totally stunned.

364
00:14:28,270 --> 00:14:29,010
I hadn't decided

365
00:14:29,010 --> 00:14:30,360
whether to dodge left or right,

366
00:14:30,360 --> 00:14:32,090
and the car just whooshed past.

367
00:14:32,370 --> 00:14:33,580
You're an honest guy.

368
00:14:33,650 --> 00:14:34,250
Right?

369
00:14:34,290 --> 00:14:35,020
But

370
00:14:35,050 --> 00:14:36,800
fortune favors fools.

371
00:14:37,270 --> 00:14:37,870
If it were me,

372
00:14:37,870 --> 00:14:39,010
whichever way I dodged,

373
00:14:39,010 --> 00:14:39,960
the car would crash that way.

374
00:14:39,960 --> 00:14:41,620
I would have been sent flying.

375
00:14:43,440 --> 00:14:43,820
Here.

376
00:14:45,360 --> 00:14:46,090
What's this?

377
00:14:46,290 --> 00:14:47,480
Someone from the Student Union
gave them to me.

378
00:14:47,480 --> 00:14:48,080
Let me see.

379
00:14:48,130 --> 00:14:48,460
Here.

380
00:14:49,600 --> 00:14:50,390
Yesterday I helped them

381
00:14:50,390 --> 00:14:51,580
guide an event all day,

382
00:14:51,580 --> 00:14:53,110
so they gave me two tickets.

383
00:14:53,750 --> 00:14:55,620
Vouchers for the Central TV & Radio Tower
trial run.

384
00:14:55,620 --> 00:14:56,890
If you sell them to scalpers,

385
00:14:56,890 --> 00:14:58,000
you could make a couple hundred.

386
00:14:58,000 --> 00:14:59,980
Why do you have
to make money on everything?

387
00:14:59,980 --> 00:15:02,120
Young people should enjoy themselves.

388
00:15:02,120 --> 00:15:03,250
Go up and have a look.

389
00:15:03,700 --> 00:15:05,080
Every time I pass by there,

390
00:15:05,080 --> 00:15:06,080
I think to myself,

391
00:15:06,220 --> 00:15:08,200
how is this tower so tall?

392
00:15:08,700 --> 00:15:09,440
People say

393
00:15:09,580 --> 00:15:10,640
that from up there,

394
00:15:10,670 --> 00:15:13,210
you can see the whole of Beijing.

395
00:15:13,480 --> 00:15:13,980
You can.

396
00:15:14,150 --> 00:15:15,050
Yes, you can see it.

397
00:15:15,050 --> 00:15:15,650
Right?

398
00:15:16,600 --> 00:15:17,550
But these are worth a lot.

399
00:15:17,550 --> 00:15:18,580
Why don't you sell them?

400
00:15:18,580 --> 00:15:19,510
You can make some money too.

401
00:15:19,510 --> 00:15:20,720
I want to go.

402
00:15:23,050 --> 00:15:23,800
Then go.

403
00:15:28,510 --> 00:15:29,420
Drink up.

404
00:15:29,860 --> 00:15:30,600
Come on.

405
00:15:30,630 --> 00:15:31,290
Count me in.

406
00:15:31,740 --> 00:15:32,340
What?

407
00:15:32,340 --> 00:15:34,410
-You two just go.
-Come on. Here.

408
00:15:34,720 --> 00:15:35,630
Here.

409
00:15:35,630 --> 00:15:36,200
Let's clink glasses!

410
00:15:36,200 --> 00:15:36,730
Cheers.

411
00:15:36,840 --> 00:15:39,050
-Cheers!
-Cheers!

412
00:15:44,410 --> 00:15:45,650
It's so tall!

413
00:15:46,010 --> 00:15:47,120
How high is this?

414
00:15:48,150 --> 00:15:48,890
Are we going

415
00:15:48,890 --> 00:15:50,030
to the very top later?

416
00:15:50,030 --> 00:15:50,860
Of course.

417
00:15:52,850 --> 00:15:54,480
Haven't you been here before?

418
00:15:54,480 --> 00:15:55,080
No.

419
00:15:55,370 --> 00:15:57,220
Didn't you come to Beijing before?

420
00:15:57,220 --> 00:15:58,360
You've never been up?

421
00:15:58,360 --> 00:15:58,950
Nope.

422
00:16:00,320 --> 00:16:01,320
Are you afraid of heights?

423
00:16:01,320 --> 00:16:02,690
Of course not.

424
00:16:03,130 --> 00:16:03,890
Why? Are you scared?

425
00:16:03,890 --> 00:16:05,390
I'm not scared.

426
00:16:06,620 --> 00:16:07,190
Okay.

427
00:16:07,720 --> 00:16:09,320
Whoever gets scared is a dog.

428
00:16:10,940 --> 00:16:11,490
Let's go!

429
00:16:11,790 --> 00:16:12,320
Let's go!

430
00:16:14,150 --> 00:16:15,010
Welcome

431
00:16:15,010 --> 00:16:16,340
everyone who's here to visit

432
00:16:16,340 --> 00:16:17,550
the Central TV & Radio Tower.

433
00:16:17,550 --> 00:16:18,700
Since this is

434
00:16:18,700 --> 00:16:19,740
a high-speed elevator,

435
00:16:19,740 --> 00:16:21,550
your ears might feel uncomfortable

436
00:16:21,550 --> 00:16:22,890
during the ride.

437
00:16:22,960 --> 00:16:24,820
You can swallow

438
00:16:24,820 --> 00:16:26,220
to relieve the pressure.

439
00:16:33,630 --> 00:16:34,290
This works.

440
00:16:41,010 --> 00:16:41,870
My ears popped.

441
00:16:42,600 --> 00:16:43,910
We have arrived. Please alight slowly.

442
00:16:43,910 --> 00:16:45,100
Watch your step.

443
00:16:46,010 --> 00:16:47,270
Hello. Welcome.

444
00:16:47,340 --> 00:16:49,510
We're at the Open-Air Observation Deck.

445
00:16:49,510 --> 00:16:51,510
Mind the steps. Watch your footing.

446
00:16:53,410 --> 00:16:54,400
It's huge!

447
00:16:56,620 --> 00:16:58,200
Come on. Let's go check over there.

448
00:16:58,200 --> 00:16:58,620
Okay.

449
00:16:58,870 --> 00:16:59,730
Zhuang Zhuang!

450
00:17:02,790 --> 00:17:03,540
What is this?

451
00:17:03,630 --> 00:17:04,530
A telescope.

452
00:17:06,720 --> 00:17:07,349
It's so clear.

453
00:17:07,349 --> 00:17:09,160
There are people dancing over there!

454
00:17:09,160 --> 00:17:09,700
Where?

455
00:17:10,460 --> 00:17:11,119
Over there.

456
00:17:11,170 --> 00:17:11,869
Have a look.

457
00:17:12,480 --> 00:17:13,579
Let me try.

458
00:17:13,579 --> 00:17:14,839
You can see really far.

459
00:17:17,250 --> 00:17:18,810
There's nothing; it's dark.

460
00:17:18,810 --> 00:17:19,609
There's nothing?

461
00:17:19,609 --> 00:17:20,140
No—

462
00:17:24,010 --> 00:17:24,940
Here, let me see.

463
00:17:27,460 --> 00:17:28,500
Look down there!

464
00:17:29,090 --> 00:17:29,690
Bayi Lake!

465
00:17:30,610 --> 00:17:31,980
Next to Bayi Lake!

466
00:17:32,050 --> 00:17:32,700
Where?

467
00:17:33,400 --> 00:17:34,500
The Military Museum!

468
00:17:34,500 --> 00:17:34,900
Look.

469
00:17:35,690 --> 00:17:36,900
To the right of the lake.

470
00:17:36,900 --> 00:17:38,100
The Military Museum.

471
00:17:38,690 --> 00:17:39,370
Do you see it?

472
00:17:39,370 --> 00:17:40,470
Where is the museum?

473
00:17:40,470 --> 00:17:41,330
To the right of that lake.

474
00:17:41,330 --> 00:17:42,250
Go right a bit.

475
00:17:43,140 --> 00:17:44,340
The Military Museum.

476
00:17:45,090 --> 00:17:46,310
Go up. Further up.

477
00:17:47,310 --> 00:17:48,240
In the distance.

478
00:17:48,840 --> 00:17:49,500
That row

479
00:17:49,520 --> 00:17:50,680
of yellow roofs

480
00:17:50,810 --> 00:17:51,400
is the Forbidden City.

481
00:17:51,400 --> 00:17:53,000
Look further left.

482
00:17:53,100 --> 00:17:54,500
A little more to the left.

483
00:17:55,040 --> 00:17:56,350
White Pagoda Temple. Do you see it?

484
00:17:56,350 --> 00:17:57,050
I see it.

485
00:17:57,240 --> 00:17:58,640
Further past the White Pagoda Temple

486
00:17:58,640 --> 00:17:59,440
is our home.

487
00:18:00,550 --> 00:18:01,900
Little Northeasterner is riding a bike

488
00:18:01,900 --> 00:18:02,610
right into the house.

489
00:18:02,610 --> 00:18:03,870
You still can't see it?

490
00:18:04,740 --> 00:18:06,270
Since when is it "our home"?

491
00:18:07,840 --> 00:18:10,150
That... That is our home.

492
00:18:10,680 --> 00:18:12,010
Seasons Change Hostel.

493
00:18:14,000 --> 00:18:15,180
You say "our home"

494
00:18:15,180 --> 00:18:16,110
so naturally.

495
00:18:17,050 --> 00:18:17,510
That...

496
00:18:17,850 --> 00:18:18,720
That's...

497
00:18:19,060 --> 00:18:20,480
a home for all of us.

498
00:18:22,570 --> 00:18:23,700
You sound so guilty.

499
00:18:24,550 --> 00:18:25,900
How so?

500
00:18:26,850 --> 00:18:28,380
Let me take a picture of you.

501
00:18:28,420 --> 00:18:29,290
You brought a camera?

502
00:18:29,290 --> 00:18:30,560
I did!

503
00:18:37,330 --> 00:18:37,790
Come on.

504
00:18:39,070 --> 00:18:41,870
One, two, three.

505
00:18:42,500 --> 00:18:42,830
Great.

506
00:18:42,830 --> 00:18:44,030
Let me take one of you.

507
00:18:44,090 --> 00:18:44,610
Okay.

508
00:18:44,680 --> 00:18:45,680
You look so happy!

509
00:18:46,010 --> 00:18:46,830
Let me take a photo

510
00:18:46,830 --> 00:18:47,940
of you two newlyweds.

511
00:18:47,940 --> 00:18:48,550
It'll be ready in an instant!

512
00:18:48,550 --> 00:18:49,600
What newlyweds?

513
00:18:49,850 --> 00:18:51,250
We're just good friends.

514
00:18:51,960 --> 00:18:53,130
All the more
you should take a photo together.

515
00:18:53,130 --> 00:18:54,110
It's so beautiful here.

516
00:18:54,110 --> 00:18:54,960
Take a picture for a keepsake!

517
00:18:54,960 --> 00:18:55,640
Come on.

518
00:18:55,940 --> 00:18:56,850
-Come on.
-We can get the photo

519
00:18:56,850 --> 00:18:58,030
after you take it?

520
00:18:58,460 --> 00:18:59,570
You can get it instantly here.

521
00:18:59,570 --> 00:19:01,130
How can film be instant?

522
00:19:01,610 --> 00:19:02,210
This here

523
00:19:02,230 --> 00:19:03,200
is the latest technology.

524
00:19:03,200 --> 00:19:04,380
I spent a fortune on it.

525
00:19:04,380 --> 00:19:05,210
It's a digital camera.

526
00:19:05,210 --> 00:19:05,940
How about it?

527
00:19:06,570 --> 00:19:07,500
Well then...

528
00:19:08,500 --> 00:19:09,060
Let's take one.

529
00:19:09,060 --> 00:19:09,630
Come on.

530
00:19:09,700 --> 00:19:11,220
-Come on. Come on.
-Closer. Closer.

531
00:19:11,220 --> 00:19:11,950
Great.

532
00:19:12,200 --> 00:19:13,000
Smile.

533
00:19:13,020 --> 00:19:14,220
Miss, give us a smile.

534
00:19:14,480 --> 00:19:16,330
Okay. Three, two, one.

535
00:19:17,150 --> 00:19:17,680
Okay.

536
00:19:17,850 --> 00:19:19,110
Beijing welcomes you.

537
00:19:19,330 --> 00:19:19,980
How much?

538
00:19:21,640 --> 00:19:22,110
Twenty.

539
00:19:23,150 --> 00:19:24,280
Twenty?

540
00:19:24,370 --> 00:19:25,700
That's way too expensive.

541
00:19:25,700 --> 00:19:26,630
It's instant.

542
00:19:26,650 --> 00:19:27,850
We'll think about it.

543
00:19:28,420 --> 00:19:29,530
-It's too expensive.
-Hey!

544
00:19:29,530 --> 00:19:30,830
Can you make it cheaper?

545
00:19:30,830 --> 00:19:33,030
-We don't want it.
-I'll keep it for you.

546
00:19:47,700 --> 00:19:49,430
You can even eat here?

547
00:19:49,960 --> 00:19:50,520
Look.

548
00:19:51,610 --> 00:19:53,410
This is a revolving restaurant?

549
00:19:54,140 --> 00:19:55,920
It rotates once every 90 minutes.

550
00:19:55,920 --> 00:19:57,240
You can see all of Beijing.

551
00:19:57,240 --> 00:19:58,100
How do you know?

552
00:19:58,440 --> 00:20:00,100
It's mentioned on the ticket.

553
00:20:02,030 --> 00:20:03,830
It doesn't look like it's turning.

554
00:20:03,830 --> 00:20:05,110
Is... Is it expensive?

555
00:20:06,880 --> 00:20:08,940
We can't afford it right now, anyway.

556
00:20:10,080 --> 00:20:11,480
Maybe when we have money.

557
00:20:25,790 --> 00:20:26,720
It's rock-hard.

558
00:20:28,080 --> 00:20:28,940
It is a bit hard.

559
00:20:34,800 --> 00:20:36,260
I'm going to the restroom.

560
00:20:36,630 --> 00:20:37,460
Wait for me.

561
00:20:38,380 --> 00:20:39,250
I'll be quick.

562
00:21:31,670 --> 00:21:32,790
Beijing is great.

563
00:21:36,920 --> 00:21:38,320
Let's work hard

564
00:21:39,250 --> 00:21:41,640
to stay in this city!

565
00:21:48,720 --> 00:21:50,180
Mr. Zheng said I can't shout.

566
00:21:50,180 --> 00:21:51,310
I have to protect my voice.

567
00:21:51,310 --> 00:21:52,640
Then I'll shout for you.

568
00:21:54,420 --> 00:21:57,880
Zhuang Zhuang is going to stay too!

569
00:22:11,010 --> 00:22:12,670
[Central TV & Radio Tower;
altitude: 405 meters]

570
00:22:14,700 --> 00:22:15,500
You bought it?

571
00:22:16,740 --> 00:22:18,400
Twenty yuan is too expensive.

572
00:22:18,980 --> 00:22:19,500
Forty.

573
00:22:27,140 --> 00:22:29,410
[Central TV & Radio Tower;
altitude: 405 meters]

574
00:22:31,980 --> 00:22:34,910
You could have spent this money
on something better.

575
00:22:50,660 --> 00:22:52,120
You're finally here, Cui.

576
00:22:52,400 --> 00:22:54,400
Your dialect is slipping out again.

577
00:22:54,970 --> 00:22:56,410
I'm just anxious.

578
00:22:56,640 --> 00:22:58,180
I'll be careful next time.

579
00:22:58,240 --> 00:23:00,030
I won't make the same mistake again.

580
00:23:00,030 --> 00:23:00,750
Look.

581
00:23:01,270 --> 00:23:02,180
This outfit you're wearing today,

582
00:23:02,180 --> 00:23:03,010
it looks so good.

583
00:23:03,010 --> 00:23:03,590
On the day of the audition,

584
00:23:03,590 --> 00:23:04,990
why didn't you wear this?

585
00:23:08,140 --> 00:23:08,830
Ranran.

586
00:23:09,240 --> 00:23:11,030
I told you over the phone.

587
00:23:11,330 --> 00:23:12,400
The director has already

588
00:23:12,400 --> 00:23:13,350
cast all the roles.

589
00:23:13,350 --> 00:23:15,350
There's really no chance this time.

590
00:23:16,660 --> 00:23:17,590
Can't you help me

591
00:23:17,590 --> 00:23:18,850
figure something out?

592
00:23:18,960 --> 00:23:19,330
Well,

593
00:23:19,810 --> 00:23:20,660
if there was a way,

594
00:23:20,660 --> 00:23:22,790
wouldn't I help you?

595
00:23:26,070 --> 00:23:27,260
Don't cry.

596
00:23:27,640 --> 00:23:28,440
Tell you what.

597
00:23:28,680 --> 00:23:29,720
Let's wait.

598
00:23:29,760 --> 00:23:30,350
Okay?

599
00:23:30,740 --> 00:23:32,500
In case something goes wrong with a role,

600
00:23:32,500 --> 00:23:33,030
or an actor

601
00:23:33,030 --> 00:23:34,220
gets a stomachache and can't come,

602
00:23:34,220 --> 00:23:35,570
they'll have to replace her.

603
00:23:35,570 --> 00:23:38,640
W-Will that really work?

604
00:23:41,220 --> 00:23:42,640
It's mostly luck.

605
00:23:47,660 --> 00:23:48,690
Don't cry.

606
00:23:52,750 --> 00:23:53,740
Passengers who have just boarded,

607
00:23:53,740 --> 00:23:54,870
please move inside!

608
00:23:54,940 --> 00:23:56,590
Take it slow. Be careful.
Don't bump into anything.

609
00:23:56,590 --> 00:23:57,200
Thank you. Thanks.

610
00:23:57,200 --> 00:23:58,860
-Excuse me.
-Tickets for two.

611
00:24:08,620 --> 00:24:09,340
You're tired?

612
00:24:09,280 --> 00:24:11,830
♪ If I want to look far away ♪

613
00:24:09,750 --> 00:24:10,280
I'm okay.

614
00:24:14,000 --> 00:24:16,570
♪ A cloud can't block the sun ♪

615
00:24:15,320 --> 00:24:16,180
[CHUN LAI JIE]

616
00:24:16,180 --> 00:24:17,490
[Develop Campus Services,
Boost Economic Growth]

617
00:24:17,700 --> 00:24:19,270
Your clothes look really beautiful.

618
00:24:19,270 --> 00:24:20,030
Of course!

619
00:24:20,030 --> 00:24:21,500
Our boss picked them all.

620
00:24:20,920 --> 00:24:24,780
♪ Go to the vast sea
with wind and waves ♪

621
00:24:26,190 --> 00:24:29,580
♪ Instead of struggling in the pond ♪

622
00:24:30,690 --> 00:24:33,340
♪ If I have faith in spring ♪

623
00:24:35,520 --> 00:24:38,250
♪ A rainstorm can't bring away
the fragrance of flowers ♪

624
00:24:42,660 --> 00:24:46,380
♪ Those dreams that are hard to realize ♪

625
00:24:47,460 --> 00:24:50,520
♪ Have taken root deep in my heart ♪

626
00:24:51,120 --> 00:24:55,250
♪ After countless times of blooming
and withering, I still plant hope ♪

627
00:24:57,870 --> 00:25:02,120
♪ Seasons change during this trip ♪

628
00:25:02,890 --> 00:25:07,560
♪ Amid the sound of footsteps,
I head into the wind of departure ♪

629
00:25:08,170 --> 00:25:10,220
♪ With youth and innocence ♪

630
00:25:10,690 --> 00:25:12,680
♪ With a faint light ♪

631
00:25:13,180 --> 00:25:16,600
♪ Light up a brighter life ♪

632
00:25:17,320 --> 00:25:21,020
♪ Spring lingers on ♪

633
00:25:22,920 --> 00:25:23,780
Seventy-five.

634
00:25:26,120 --> 00:25:27,750
Also 75. Perfect.

635
00:25:28,980 --> 00:25:30,110
Let me measure this.

636
00:25:32,660 --> 00:25:33,570
Thirty-nine.

637
00:25:33,610 --> 00:25:35,090
Thirty-nine.

638
00:25:35,750 --> 00:25:36,500
Zongbao!

639
00:25:37,000 --> 00:25:38,830
Why did you move my cabinet over there?

640
00:25:38,830 --> 00:25:40,140
Wait. Come on, give me a hand.

641
00:25:40,140 --> 00:25:40,860
No, no, no.

642
00:25:40,940 --> 00:25:41,430
Well...

643
00:25:41,550 --> 00:25:43,210
I... I need it for writing.

644
00:25:43,770 --> 00:25:45,470
I'm setting up a desk for you.

645
00:25:45,560 --> 00:25:46,430
Setting up a...

646
00:25:46,700 --> 00:25:48,010
-Don't bother. This is enough for me.
-No, no, no.

647
00:25:48,010 --> 00:25:49,510
From now... From now on,

648
00:25:49,940 --> 00:25:51,690
we're swapping beds.

649
00:25:51,810 --> 00:25:52,740
You sleep there.

650
00:25:53,610 --> 00:25:54,610
Zongbao, there's no need.

651
00:25:54,610 --> 00:25:55,830
I'm used to sleeping here.

652
00:25:55,830 --> 00:25:57,140
It's fine for me to w-write here.

653
00:25:57,140 --> 00:25:57,920
This is just fine.

654
00:25:57,920 --> 00:26:00,120
You... It's fine for you, but not for us.

655
00:26:00,550 --> 00:26:02,180
Every night, you stay up late

656
00:26:02,440 --> 00:26:04,090
h-here with the light on.

657
00:26:04,090 --> 00:26:05,580
We can't hang on anymore.

658
00:26:06,250 --> 00:26:07,430
Besides, seeing you

659
00:26:07,610 --> 00:26:08,920
sit on the floor

660
00:26:08,920 --> 00:26:10,720
and write all the time over there

661
00:26:10,750 --> 00:26:12,930
makes me feel bad.

662
00:26:13,250 --> 00:26:13,780
You know?

663
00:26:13,980 --> 00:26:16,150
You have to protect your back.

664
00:26:16,290 --> 00:26:16,700
Right?

665
00:26:16,700 --> 00:26:18,580
I just failed to protect my back

666
00:26:18,660 --> 00:26:19,680
at your age.

667
00:26:20,160 --> 00:26:21,360
Come on. Move it over.

668
00:26:22,140 --> 00:26:23,070
Come on.

669
00:26:23,220 --> 00:26:24,190
Give me a hand.

670
00:26:24,250 --> 00:26:24,750
But Zongbao,

671
00:26:24,750 --> 00:26:26,740
Liangliang and Heretic Cao aren't around.

672
00:26:26,740 --> 00:26:27,720
Is this appropriate?

673
00:26:27,720 --> 00:26:29,030
We unanimously

674
00:26:29,030 --> 00:26:31,820
agreed on swapping beds.

675
00:26:32,740 --> 00:26:33,390
I

676
00:26:33,510 --> 00:26:35,380
represent the two of them.

677
00:26:36,030 --> 00:26:36,630
And you are

678
00:26:36,750 --> 00:26:38,810
in charge of execution. Is that fine?

679
00:26:39,830 --> 00:26:41,160
Fine by me!

680
00:26:41,160 --> 00:26:41,610
Fine!

681
00:26:41,610 --> 00:26:42,310
-Fine, right?
-Yes!

682
00:26:42,310 --> 00:26:43,590
Then sit down and try it.

683
00:26:43,590 --> 00:26:44,640
Check the distance.

684
00:26:44,640 --> 00:26:45,680
See if it fits.

685
00:26:46,550 --> 00:26:47,590
Closer. Move a bit closer.

686
00:26:47,590 --> 00:26:48,240
Closer.

687
00:26:48,270 --> 00:26:49,750
Closer.

688
00:26:52,070 --> 00:26:52,950
-Okay.
-Good.

689
00:26:53,390 --> 00:26:54,750
This works. This is good.

690
00:26:54,750 --> 00:26:55,510
From now on,

691
00:26:55,510 --> 00:26:57,240
this will be your little world.

692
00:26:59,720 --> 00:27:00,750
As the old saying goes,

693
00:27:00,750 --> 00:27:02,610
only family enters the same door.

694
00:27:02,980 --> 00:27:03,640
Let me do it.

695
00:27:03,640 --> 00:27:05,600
Conversely,

696
00:27:05,900 --> 00:27:07,010
once you enter the same door,

697
00:27:07,010 --> 00:27:08,290
you'll be family.

698
00:27:08,420 --> 00:27:08,960
Right?

699
00:27:09,030 --> 00:27:10,500
Come on. Swap the beds.

700
00:27:11,550 --> 00:27:12,690
From now on,

701
00:27:12,770 --> 00:27:13,900
you'll be No. 3 here.

702
00:27:14,250 --> 00:27:16,580
Xu Sanli. ("San" means three in Chinese.)

703
00:27:16,750 --> 00:27:18,380
Liangliang and I are the same age.

704
00:27:18,380 --> 00:27:21,050
-He's even several months older than me.
-His psychological age is

705
00:27:21,050 --> 00:27:22,180
younger than yours.

706
00:27:23,900 --> 00:27:24,430
Alright!

707
00:27:25,090 --> 00:27:26,180
Xu Sanli it is!

708
00:27:29,180 --> 00:27:29,900
Mr. Xu!

709
00:27:31,770 --> 00:27:32,500
Mr. Xu!

710
00:27:33,010 --> 00:27:33,810
Give me a hand.

711
00:27:37,310 --> 00:27:38,840
That's nice treatment!

712
00:27:38,870 --> 00:27:40,050
Isn't this the freezer from the store

713
00:27:39,420 --> 00:27:43,720
[Ice lolly & Ice Cream]

714
00:27:40,050 --> 00:27:41,270
by the school's west gate?

715
00:27:41,270 --> 00:27:42,990
Yeah. Push it in a bit.

716
00:27:43,870 --> 00:27:48,400
[Ice lolly & Ice Cream]

717
00:27:45,080 --> 00:27:45,520
I just

718
00:27:45,550 --> 00:27:47,210
wanted to boost our business.

719
00:27:47,380 --> 00:27:48,380
So I rented this

720
00:27:48,460 --> 00:27:49,750
for 10 yuan a day.

721
00:27:49,880 --> 00:27:51,010
The sales go to them.

722
00:27:51,050 --> 00:27:52,570
We just want the foot traffic.

723
00:27:52,570 --> 00:27:53,820
Impressive!

724
00:27:53,920 --> 00:27:56,170
As virtue rises 1 foot, vice rises 10.

725
00:27:56,190 --> 00:27:57,470
Is that a compliment?

726
00:27:58,400 --> 00:28:00,420
Then let's say, as vice rises 1foot,

727
00:28:00,680 --> 00:28:01,400
virtue rises 10.

728
00:28:01,400 --> 00:28:02,380
Just eat.

729
00:28:02,570 --> 00:28:03,940
You've been out in the sun for a while.

730
00:28:03,940 --> 00:28:04,670
Thanks.

731
00:28:05,660 --> 00:28:07,320
Did we sell anything just now?

732
00:28:07,380 --> 00:28:07,810
No.

733
00:28:16,510 --> 00:28:17,310
Why is business

734
00:28:17,310 --> 00:28:18,370
so good over there?

735
00:28:18,770 --> 00:28:19,810
They sell jerseys.

736
00:28:19,810 --> 00:28:20,530
It's the World Cup.

737
00:28:20,530 --> 00:28:21,330
The World Cup?

738
00:28:23,030 --> 00:28:25,830
Does it have anything to do
with our national team?

739
00:28:26,590 --> 00:28:27,450
Good question.

740
00:28:27,810 --> 00:28:29,570
I'll reward you with an ice cream.

741
00:28:29,570 --> 00:28:30,510
I don't want it.

742
00:28:30,610 --> 00:28:31,610
-It's on me.
-I...

743
00:28:31,700 --> 00:28:32,240
My treat.

744
00:28:36,550 --> 00:28:38,480
Spending money before making any.

745
00:28:38,510 --> 00:28:40,170
How much can an ice cream cost?

746
00:28:51,900 --> 00:28:53,630
About your tuition this month,

747
00:28:54,310 --> 00:28:55,640
I actually have an idea.

748
00:28:56,900 --> 00:28:57,640
What idea?

749
00:29:00,890 --> 00:29:01,600
Argentina.

750
00:29:04,070 --> 00:29:04,900
Argentina?

751
00:29:05,190 --> 00:29:05,580
Yes.

752
00:29:07,070 --> 00:29:09,460
How come you still
haven't gotten a role yet?

753
00:29:09,460 --> 00:29:10,860
It's not that easy.

754
00:29:11,590 --> 00:29:12,590
Ranran,

755
00:29:12,680 --> 00:29:14,540
look at you after all these years.

756
00:29:14,750 --> 00:29:15,350
Tell me...

757
00:29:16,000 --> 00:29:17,430
You're all grown up,

758
00:29:17,480 --> 00:29:19,680
but you can't share any of my burden.

759
00:29:20,590 --> 00:29:22,520
I fed you, clothed you,

760
00:29:22,550 --> 00:29:24,900
and supported you to go to Beijing
to make a mark.

761
00:29:24,900 --> 00:29:26,580
Do you think it's easy for me?

762
00:29:26,830 --> 00:29:27,500
Mom,

763
00:29:28,200 --> 00:29:29,350
this is Beijing.

764
00:29:29,350 --> 00:29:30,500
I'm a new actress.

765
00:29:30,500 --> 00:29:32,330
It's hard for me to get roles.

766
00:29:32,470 --> 00:29:33,270
Well,

767
00:29:33,590 --> 00:29:34,510
over the years,

768
00:29:34,560 --> 00:29:36,310
I've spent so much money

769
00:29:36,380 --> 00:29:37,750
on your acting classes!

770
00:29:38,310 --> 00:29:39,480
Don't tell me

771
00:29:39,480 --> 00:29:40,400
this was a losing deal

772
00:29:40,400 --> 00:29:41,930
now that you're in Beijing!

773
00:29:42,180 --> 00:29:43,380
You money pit.

774
00:29:43,630 --> 00:29:44,960
I'm not a money pit.

775
00:29:44,960 --> 00:29:46,660
You're calling me that again.

776
00:29:49,010 --> 00:29:50,480
How about this? I'll pay the rent

777
00:29:50,480 --> 00:29:51,050
for this month

778
00:29:51,050 --> 00:29:52,420
and then go back to Huzhou
to work in the factory.

779
00:29:52,420 --> 00:29:53,150
Is that okay?

780
00:29:53,440 --> 00:29:54,500
Alright, alright.

781
00:29:54,810 --> 00:29:56,010
This is the last time.

782
00:30:08,590 --> 00:30:09,350
Sir, you got your jerseys

783
00:30:09,350 --> 00:30:10,480
from a street stall, didn't you?

784
00:30:10,480 --> 00:30:11,610
It's too expensive!

785
00:30:11,790 --> 00:30:12,380
Give me a discount.

786
00:30:12,380 --> 00:30:13,090
I'll buy it if it's cheaper.

787
00:30:13,090 --> 00:30:14,330
Look at this. Look.

788
00:30:14,380 --> 00:30:15,960
This is the real deal
made for export and sold locally.

789
00:30:15,960 --> 00:30:17,010
I just got these from the Port of Tianjin.

790
00:30:17,010 --> 00:30:17,680
yesterday.

791
00:30:17,770 --> 00:30:18,460
Shipped from the Port of Tianjin?

792
00:30:18,460 --> 00:30:20,000
Yes! You think 35 yuan per piece is

793
00:30:20,000 --> 00:30:20,590
too pricey?

794
00:30:20,590 --> 00:30:21,460
It's not expensive at all!

795
00:30:21,460 --> 00:30:22,050
How about 33?

796
00:30:22,050 --> 00:30:23,050
I'll take 2 pieces for 33 yuan each.

797
00:30:23,050 --> 00:30:24,030
I want one! Give me one!

798
00:30:24,030 --> 00:30:25,040
I want to buy it!

799
00:30:25,110 --> 00:30:26,770
You want to sell jerseys, too?

800
00:30:27,700 --> 00:30:29,830
Yes, and only the Argentina team ones.

801
00:30:30,220 --> 00:30:34,970
[Ice lolly & Ice Cream]

802
00:30:31,400 --> 00:30:32,530
I have connections.

803
00:30:32,570 --> 00:30:33,900
I know someone at the factory.

804
00:30:33,900 --> 00:30:34,750
That's great.

805
00:30:34,850 --> 00:30:36,550
Wait, only Argentina?

806
00:30:37,140 --> 00:30:39,250
This is our star product.

807
00:30:39,740 --> 00:30:40,640
Don't you know?

808
00:30:40,770 --> 00:30:41,770
This year's hot favorite

809
00:30:41,770 --> 00:30:42,900
to win is Argentina.

810
00:30:43,500 --> 00:30:44,830
Do you know Maradona?

811
00:30:44,980 --> 00:30:46,080
Maradona?

812
00:30:46,240 --> 00:30:47,720
Sounds like Malatang.

813
00:30:48,160 --> 00:30:49,480
It's "Maradona."

814
00:30:51,480 --> 00:30:52,120
Look.

815
00:30:52,960 --> 00:30:54,740
So many people are buying them now.

816
00:30:54,740 --> 00:30:56,120
We're already late.

817
00:30:56,770 --> 00:30:58,300
To rake in profits in one go,

818
00:30:58,570 --> 00:30:59,570
we have to be bold.

819
00:30:59,760 --> 00:31:05,800
[Ice lolly & Ice Cream]

820
00:31:00,250 --> 00:31:01,310
The last World Cup.

821
00:31:01,840 --> 00:31:03,040
In the last World Cup,

822
00:31:03,110 --> 00:31:04,770
Argentina was the runner-up.

823
00:31:05,180 --> 00:31:07,210
They're really hungry for victory now.

824
00:31:07,210 --> 00:31:09,140
Maradona is

825
00:31:10,160 --> 00:31:11,160
on fire this year.

826
00:31:11,460 --> 00:31:12,860
Is that your inside info?

827
00:31:14,900 --> 00:31:16,230
Han Qiaosheng also said so.

828
00:31:16,230 --> 00:31:17,420
Who is Han Qiaosheng?

829
00:31:17,420 --> 00:31:18,380
A football commentator.

830
00:31:18,380 --> 00:31:19,880
Then why are you whispering?

831
00:31:19,880 --> 00:31:21,010
Doesn't the whole country know that then?

832
00:31:21,010 --> 00:31:21,640
Exactly.

833
00:31:21,680 --> 00:31:22,940
I-I just felt that it fit the vibe

834
00:31:22,940 --> 00:31:24,400
b-between the three of us.

835
00:31:25,820 --> 00:31:33,590
[Ice lolly & Ice Cream]

836
00:31:26,750 --> 00:31:27,160
Look.

837
00:31:27,810 --> 00:31:29,880
There are a lot of student football fans.

838
00:31:29,880 --> 00:31:32,610
I think we should only sell jerseys then.

839
00:31:32,920 --> 00:31:33,550
I promise

840
00:31:34,140 --> 00:31:36,070
we'll make our money back overnight.

841
00:31:36,070 --> 00:31:36,960
Since you put it that way,

842
00:31:36,960 --> 00:31:38,110
should I stock a few, too?

843
00:31:38,110 --> 00:31:38,970
Sure.

844
00:31:40,030 --> 00:31:41,480
I sell women's clothing.

845
00:31:41,980 --> 00:31:43,850
Then you'll miss the chance

846
00:31:43,870 --> 00:31:44,870
to make a fortune.

847
00:31:45,330 --> 00:31:46,700
Do you think I'm a money-grubber?

848
00:31:46,700 --> 00:31:47,700
I'll make the call for you right now

849
00:31:47,700 --> 00:31:48,560
to carry it out.

850
00:31:48,940 --> 00:31:49,350
Nice!

851
00:31:50,070 --> 00:31:51,000
Thank you, miss!

852
00:31:52,920 --> 00:31:55,180
Do we really only get the Argentina ones?

853
00:32:02,460 --> 00:32:02,920
Fine.

854
00:32:21,000 --> 00:32:21,640
Hey, girl.

855
00:32:22,180 --> 00:32:22,980
What's wrong?

856
00:32:23,610 --> 00:32:24,470
Are you crying?

857
00:32:26,050 --> 00:32:27,450
D-Did someone bully you?

858
00:32:27,900 --> 00:32:29,360
I'm rehearsing in my head.

859
00:32:30,480 --> 00:32:31,880
Rehearsing in your head?

860
00:32:32,550 --> 00:32:33,400
If you ask me,

861
00:32:33,810 --> 00:32:35,700
you don't even need to do it.

862
00:32:36,530 --> 00:32:38,410
Your every expression is

863
00:32:38,570 --> 00:32:39,650
full of drama.

864
00:32:41,000 --> 00:32:42,290
Even you can tell

865
00:32:42,290 --> 00:32:43,840
that I'm a natural actress.

866
00:32:44,920 --> 00:32:46,860
That director is just blind.

867
00:32:48,250 --> 00:32:49,100
S-So...

868
00:32:49,270 --> 00:32:51,390
So you failed to get the role?

869
00:32:51,830 --> 00:32:53,270
It's okay, girl.

870
00:32:53,700 --> 00:32:55,310
Do you know

871
00:32:55,640 --> 00:32:58,990
h-how many movies
the film studio makes a year?

872
00:32:59,140 --> 00:33:00,520
Dozens.

873
00:33:00,830 --> 00:33:01,900
If this one doesn't work out,

874
00:33:01,900 --> 00:33:03,300
w-we'll get the next one.

875
00:33:04,290 --> 00:33:06,430
Several movies, and not one picked me.

876
00:33:06,570 --> 00:33:07,080
No,

877
00:33:07,610 --> 00:33:09,070
that's not what I meant.

878
00:33:09,290 --> 00:33:09,880
Girl,

879
00:33:10,050 --> 00:33:12,040
when w-we act,

880
00:33:12,180 --> 00:33:14,240
w-we can't only fixate on those roles,

881
00:33:14,240 --> 00:33:15,370
the ones with lines.

882
00:33:15,790 --> 00:33:17,700
Let's look at the ones without lines.

883
00:33:17,700 --> 00:33:18,290
Right?

884
00:33:18,420 --> 00:33:19,960
Just think about... about...

885
00:33:19,960 --> 00:33:20,980
life.

886
00:33:21,160 --> 00:33:22,760
It's about 30,000 days long.

887
00:33:22,980 --> 00:33:24,780
The key is to experience, right?

888
00:33:24,780 --> 00:33:26,140
Y-You should try to experience

889
00:33:26,140 --> 00:33:27,940
the ones without lines, like...

890
00:33:28,110 --> 00:33:29,580
Like a corpse, right?

891
00:33:29,660 --> 00:33:31,180
Or someone hanging themselves.

892
00:33:31,180 --> 00:33:31,850
Or those buried alive...

893
00:33:31,850 --> 00:33:33,880
Can you please
think of something better for me?

894
00:33:33,880 --> 00:33:35,540
Yes, yes, there are good ones.

895
00:33:35,610 --> 00:33:37,290
Right. Then let's p-play roles with lines.

896
00:33:37,290 --> 00:33:39,040
L-Let's do the... the...

897
00:33:39,180 --> 00:33:40,380
The fighting scenes.

898
00:33:40,400 --> 00:33:41,510
Those shooting guns, right?

899
00:33:41,510 --> 00:33:44,070
Let's play servants to the Emperor

900
00:33:44,550 --> 00:33:45,510
or the Empress.

901
00:33:45,510 --> 00:33:46,710
Come, Your Highness.

902
00:33:46,740 --> 00:33:48,410
The steps are too high.

903
00:33:48,440 --> 00:33:49,680
C-Come on down.

904
00:33:49,830 --> 00:33:50,500
Your Highness.

905
00:33:50,500 --> 00:33:51,310
Come on. Come down.

906
00:33:51,310 --> 00:33:52,000
No, I won't go down.

907
00:33:52,000 --> 00:33:52,660
Come down, come down.

908
00:33:52,660 --> 00:33:53,900
Come on, come down now.

909
00:33:53,900 --> 00:33:54,960
Come down, come on.

910
00:33:55,480 --> 00:33:56,680
What's going on here?

911
00:33:57,640 --> 00:33:58,400
Guo,

912
00:33:58,900 --> 00:34:00,050
don't get fresh.

913
00:34:00,050 --> 00:34:01,230
You have a family.

914
00:34:01,380 --> 00:34:03,220
What are you talking about? You...

915
00:34:03,220 --> 00:34:04,380
This girl... Well...

916
00:34:04,380 --> 00:34:05,840
Um, she went to an audition

917
00:34:05,850 --> 00:34:07,140
and didn't get the role.

918
00:34:07,140 --> 00:34:09,639
I was just comforting her.

919
00:34:16,480 --> 00:34:17,940
I thought it was a big deal.

920
00:34:18,210 --> 00:34:20,070
So it's just that the director
didn't pick you.

921
00:34:20,070 --> 00:34:21,530
We didn't like him either!

922
00:34:21,860 --> 00:34:23,130
If not this time, then next time.

923
00:34:23,130 --> 00:34:23,530
Right.

924
00:34:23,800 --> 00:34:25,659
You have to learn from Guo on this.

925
00:34:25,860 --> 00:34:26,719
Look at Mr. Guo.

926
00:34:27,030 --> 00:34:27,800
He's been waiting at the gate

927
00:34:27,800 --> 00:34:28,570
of the film studio for years.

928
00:34:28,570 --> 00:34:29,460
What roles has he played?

929
00:34:29,460 --> 00:34:31,340
He hasn't gotten a single role as well!

930
00:34:31,340 --> 00:34:32,820
But he has a good mindset. Look.

931
00:34:32,820 --> 00:34:33,719
Nice and plump.

932
00:34:33,860 --> 00:34:34,190
Look.

933
00:34:34,230 --> 00:34:36,190
I-It's mainly

934
00:34:36,280 --> 00:34:37,800
because of my back problems, right?

935
00:34:37,800 --> 00:34:39,000
I dare not exercise, right?

936
00:34:39,000 --> 00:34:40,000
It's because you're chill.

937
00:34:40,000 --> 00:34:40,530
Chill.

938
00:34:40,900 --> 00:34:42,360
How many years has it been?

939
00:34:43,260 --> 00:34:44,460
Then wouldn't I...

940
00:34:46,300 --> 00:34:48,429
Then I'm even more hopeless, aren't I?

941
00:34:48,690 --> 00:34:49,500
Girl, girl!

942
00:34:49,590 --> 00:34:51,420
Girl, that's not what I meant.

943
00:34:51,500 --> 00:34:52,630
What I'm saying is,

944
00:34:52,630 --> 00:34:54,190
don't compare yourself
to people better off than you.

945
00:34:54,190 --> 00:34:55,710
Compare yourself to those worse off!

946
00:34:55,710 --> 00:34:57,130
What are you talking about?

947
00:34:57,130 --> 00:34:58,940
Look at the people living in the basement.

948
00:34:58,940 --> 00:35:00,780
Who among them doesn't feel frustrated?

949
00:35:00,780 --> 00:35:02,570
Every single one of them aims high,

950
00:35:02,570 --> 00:35:03,830
but has a fragile fate.

951
00:35:04,860 --> 00:35:05,930
Well, he... he...

952
00:35:05,980 --> 00:35:07,790
Well, he's frustrated too!

953
00:35:08,130 --> 00:35:09,530
I... I'm not frustrated.

954
00:35:10,030 --> 00:35:11,830
Why wouldn't you be frustrated?

955
00:35:13,400 --> 00:35:14,670
Right, I'm frustrated too!

956
00:35:14,670 --> 00:35:15,600
I'm frustrated!

957
00:35:15,780 --> 00:35:16,960
What are you frustrated about?

958
00:35:16,960 --> 00:35:17,340
I...

959
00:35:18,090 --> 00:35:19,110
He... What am I frustrated about?

960
00:35:19,110 --> 00:35:19,550
He...

961
00:35:19,940 --> 00:35:21,260
He... well...

962
00:35:21,400 --> 00:35:22,890
When the boss comes,

963
00:35:22,980 --> 00:35:24,250
his face...

964
00:35:24,380 --> 00:35:26,300
faces the boss like this.

965
00:35:27,300 --> 00:35:28,610
But when the boss turns away,

966
00:35:28,610 --> 00:35:30,010
his face changes to this.

967
00:35:30,230 --> 00:35:30,800
Right?

968
00:35:32,380 --> 00:35:33,610
Look, she smiled. Look.

969
00:35:33,610 --> 00:35:34,400
Come down, come down.

970
00:35:34,400 --> 00:35:35,230
Come down, come down.

971
00:35:35,230 --> 00:35:36,170
I'm fine!

972
00:35:40,340 --> 00:35:41,460
Do you two think

973
00:35:41,460 --> 00:35:42,650
I'm going to die here?

974
00:35:42,650 --> 00:35:43,190
If I were to jump,

975
00:35:43,190 --> 00:35:43,960
I wouldn't die

976
00:35:43,960 --> 00:35:45,050
in this courtyard.

977
00:35:45,150 --> 00:35:46,570
This... this looks pretty dangerous.

978
00:35:46,570 --> 00:35:47,030
You...

979
00:35:47,090 --> 00:35:49,190
I just wanted to look at the sky

980
00:35:49,300 --> 00:35:50,900
and get some fresh air.

981
00:35:51,570 --> 00:35:52,940
That's more like it, girl.

982
00:35:52,940 --> 00:35:53,730
Even if we jump,

983
00:35:53,730 --> 00:35:54,490
we shouldn't do in this courtyard.

984
00:35:54,490 --> 00:35:55,610
Jump in someone else's courtyard.

985
00:35:55,610 --> 00:35:56,800
-You...
-What are you saying?

986
00:35:56,800 --> 00:35:57,570
Look.

987
00:35:57,900 --> 00:35:59,570
I have a chilled watermelon over there.

988
00:35:59,570 --> 00:36:00,550
I'll cut it open.

989
00:36:00,780 --> 00:36:01,570
Let's have some watermelon.

990
00:36:01,570 --> 00:36:03,290
-Let's not stay out here in the sun.
- Have some watermelon!

991
00:36:03,290 --> 00:36:04,670
I'll come down and eat later.

992
00:36:04,670 --> 00:36:06,260
I want to stay here a little longer.

993
00:36:06,260 --> 00:36:07,260
You guys go ahead.

994
00:36:07,280 --> 00:36:08,480
Okay, come down soon!

995
00:36:08,650 --> 00:36:10,030
I'll go cut the watermelon.

996
00:36:10,030 --> 00:36:10,910
It's all right.

997
00:36:11,440 --> 00:36:12,500
Don't cry anymore.

998
00:36:14,570 --> 00:36:15,300
Go on, get busy.

999
00:36:15,300 --> 00:36:16,260
Wipe your tears.

1000
00:36:17,110 --> 00:36:17,910
It's all gone.

1001
00:36:18,070 --> 00:36:19,270
If anything happens,

1002
00:36:19,440 --> 00:36:20,340
tell me.

1003
00:36:22,730 --> 00:36:23,460
Look at this.

1004
00:36:23,690 --> 00:36:25,070
You scared me so much,

1005
00:36:25,190 --> 00:36:28,190
my clothes got all wrinkled up
from me clutching them.

1006
00:36:32,860 --> 00:36:34,120
Have some watermelon!

1007
00:36:40,280 --> 00:36:41,300
Sit a bit lower.

1008
00:36:41,300 --> 00:36:41,940
Lower, lower.

1009
00:36:41,940 --> 00:36:43,130
Can this outfit sell well?

1010
00:36:43,130 --> 00:36:44,400
Of course we can, why not?

1011
00:36:44,400 --> 00:36:45,030
After getting my hair cut,

1012
00:36:45,030 --> 00:36:45,610
it just feels like...

1013
00:36:45,610 --> 00:36:47,300
I permed my hair for him.

1014
00:36:47,300 --> 00:36:48,800
I permed it, and he cut his hair.

1015
00:36:48,800 --> 00:36:49,670
What are you even talking about?

1016
00:36:49,670 --> 00:36:51,010
Has the livestream started?

1017
00:36:51,010 --> 00:36:52,090
Just started, just started.

1018
00:36:52,090 --> 00:36:52,570
Hurry.

1019
00:36:55,820 --> 00:36:57,460
Where did you get these clothes?

1020
00:36:57,460 --> 00:36:58,610
We sourced them ourselves.

1021
00:36:58,610 --> 00:36:59,650
You two must be turning heads everywhere.

1022
00:36:59,650 --> 00:37:00,820
This is so cool!

1023
00:37:00,820 --> 00:37:01,940
Of course!

1024
00:37:01,940 --> 00:37:02,670
Do you have more?

1025
00:37:02,670 --> 00:37:03,400
Don't touch!

1026
00:37:03,590 --> 00:37:04,840
Argentina is really trending right now.

1027
00:37:04,840 --> 00:37:05,710
They sell one of these outside for

1028
00:37:05,710 --> 00:37:07,190
forty or fifty.

1029
00:37:07,380 --> 00:37:09,050
Are you charging us?

1030
00:37:09,090 --> 00:37:10,260
What else would we do?

1031
00:37:10,260 --> 00:37:11,010
How much?

1032
00:37:12,820 --> 00:37:14,010
The, the cost price...

1033
00:37:14,010 --> 00:37:14,530
Fine.

1034
00:37:14,940 --> 00:37:15,650
Thirty-five.

1035
00:37:15,650 --> 00:37:17,260
Thirty-five is the cost price!

1036
00:37:17,260 --> 00:37:18,720
Thirty-five?

1037
00:37:19,360 --> 00:37:20,550
Are you crazy?

1038
00:37:20,550 --> 00:37:21,530
Forget it if you don't want it. Here.

1039
00:37:21,530 --> 00:37:22,400
I'll take one. I'll take one.

1040
00:37:22,400 --> 00:37:23,000
You want one?

1041
00:37:23,000 --> 00:37:23,530
I'll take one.

1042
00:37:23,530 --> 00:37:24,630
You... you want number 10?

1043
00:37:24,630 --> 00:37:25,500
What can I do? I like it.

1044
00:37:25,500 --> 00:37:26,270
Right?

1045
00:37:26,690 --> 00:37:27,600
He's my idol.

1046
00:37:28,110 --> 00:37:28,710
Here, here.

1047
00:37:28,710 --> 00:37:29,570
Okay, okay, okay.

1048
00:37:29,570 --> 00:37:30,970
All eyes on him this year.

1049
00:37:31,170 --> 00:37:31,700
Shengli.

1050
00:37:32,150 --> 00:37:33,900
I... I want one too.

1051
00:37:33,900 --> 00:37:35,430
Then take one. Pay me later.

1052
00:37:35,780 --> 00:37:36,190
Okay.

1053
00:37:39,090 --> 00:37:39,420
What's wrong?

1054
00:37:39,420 --> 00:37:40,460
He doesn't have money, but I do.

1055
00:37:40,460 --> 00:37:41,000
Get me one!

1056
00:37:41,000 --> 00:37:42,460
Sell... sell it first, sell it first.

1057
00:37:42,460 --> 00:37:42,990
Alright.

1058
00:37:43,190 --> 00:37:43,840
Get me one too.

1059
00:37:43,840 --> 00:37:45,240
You too? You want one too?

1060
00:37:45,630 --> 00:37:46,880
Perfect, no need for change.

1061
00:37:46,880 --> 00:37:47,860
You look like a basketball player.

1062
00:37:47,860 --> 00:37:48,400
Who else wants one?

1063
00:37:48,400 --> 00:37:49,980
Zhuang Zhuang, I'll take one too.

1064
00:37:49,980 --> 00:37:50,590
Get me one as well.

1065
00:37:50,590 --> 00:37:51,230
-Okay!
-Two pieces, right?

1066
00:37:51,230 --> 00:37:52,560
Two pieces. Two pieces.

1067
00:37:52,920 --> 00:37:53,720
Here, take it.

1068
00:37:55,110 --> 00:37:56,110
It's starting!

1069
00:37:56,110 --> 00:37:57,500
-The quality's really good.
-Come to me if you need more.

1070
00:37:57,500 --> 00:37:58,250
Of course.

1071
00:37:58,320 --> 00:37:59,250
Plenty in stock!

1072
00:38:01,320 --> 00:38:02,050
How is it?

1073
00:38:02,130 --> 00:38:03,670
I told you it would work.

1074
00:38:03,710 --> 00:38:04,820
They really sell.

1075
00:38:05,000 --> 00:38:05,650
Xu.

1076
00:38:05,760 --> 00:38:07,090
Let me get one on credit.

1077
00:38:07,090 --> 00:38:08,710
On credit? Not a chance.

1078
00:38:08,710 --> 00:38:09,910
Just watch your game.

1079
00:38:10,570 --> 00:38:11,480
You should get number 9.

1080
00:38:11,480 --> 00:38:13,280
You kind of look like Batistuta.

1081
00:38:16,360 --> 00:38:18,220
You two like watching soccer too?

1082
00:38:19,210 --> 00:38:20,800
We do now.

1083
00:38:21,760 --> 00:38:22,230
Nice.

1084
00:38:22,840 --> 00:38:23,960
Good taste.

1085
00:38:24,300 --> 00:38:26,230
No wonder you two are making money.

1086
00:38:31,000 --> 00:38:32,030
We have so much stock.

1087
00:38:32,030 --> 00:38:34,340
Should we borrow a vehicle
to transport it?

1088
00:38:34,340 --> 00:38:36,440
A bike would be convenient.

1089
00:38:39,860 --> 00:38:41,390
I'll borrow a bike from you.

1090
00:38:43,110 --> 00:38:44,190
For the sake of these clothes,

1091
00:38:44,190 --> 00:38:44,940
take the bike and use it.

1092
00:38:44,940 --> 00:38:47,010
You're doing this for my clothes? You...

1093
00:38:47,010 --> 00:38:47,960
For the clothes.

1094
00:38:51,090 --> 00:38:51,860
Nice shot!

1095
00:38:53,280 --> 00:38:53,820
So close.

1096
00:38:57,610 --> 00:38:58,980
Yes. Hold it there.

1097
00:38:59,670 --> 00:39:00,600
Okay. It's back.

1098
00:39:01,500 --> 00:39:03,630
-Okay, okay, don't move!
-Don't move.

1099
00:39:06,130 --> 00:39:06,960
Oh my god!

1100
00:39:07,420 --> 00:39:08,480
No, just stand there and don't move.

1101
00:39:08,480 --> 00:39:09,860
You don't... Just stand there.

1102
00:39:09,860 --> 00:39:10,880
Maradona, that's him.

1103
00:39:10,880 --> 00:39:11,460
That's him.

1104
00:39:11,460 --> 00:39:12,030
I can't just

1105
00:39:12,030 --> 00:39:13,490
stand here forever, can I?

1106
00:39:14,050 --> 00:39:14,850
Wait a second.

1107
00:39:15,070 --> 00:39:16,400
You're going to snap it.

1108
00:39:16,530 --> 00:39:18,130
Alright, alright, alright.

1109
00:39:18,280 --> 00:39:19,010
Much better.

1110
00:39:19,820 --> 00:39:20,820
There's a replay.

1111
00:39:24,110 --> 00:39:24,940
He's down.

1112
00:39:25,170 --> 00:39:26,760
This should be a throw-in, right?

1113
00:39:26,760 --> 00:39:27,170
No.

1114
00:39:27,230 --> 00:39:28,210
This should be a free kick.

1115
00:39:28,210 --> 00:39:29,410
That's a yellow card.

1116
00:39:35,150 --> 00:39:36,210
What's that about?

1117
00:39:36,440 --> 00:39:37,500
What's that about?

1118
00:39:39,940 --> 00:39:40,900
Disgusting!

1119
00:39:41,170 --> 00:39:42,150
So disgusting!

1120
00:39:42,460 --> 00:39:45,300
[Seasons Change Hostel]

1121
00:39:46,460 --> 00:39:48,130
So disgusting!

1122
00:39:50,590 --> 00:39:52,340
[Seasons Change Hostel]

1123
00:39:59,980 --> 00:40:00,770
Again!

1124
00:40:32,050 --> 00:40:33,780
Yeah, I don't have class today.

1125
00:40:33,860 --> 00:40:34,870
Is the shop busy?

1126
00:40:35,480 --> 00:40:36,280
Not too bad.

1127
00:40:36,550 --> 00:40:38,280
You're running low on tuition, aren't you?

1128
00:40:38,280 --> 00:40:38,780
I didn't expect

1129
00:40:38,780 --> 00:40:40,640
to have so many classes each week.

1130
00:40:41,190 --> 00:40:42,920
I'll wire you some money tomorrow.

1131
00:40:42,920 --> 00:40:43,790
Don't worry.

1132
00:40:44,340 --> 00:40:45,960
If the teacher is willing to
give you extra lessons,

1133
00:40:45,960 --> 00:40:47,090
that's a good thing.

1134
00:40:47,230 --> 00:40:48,090
No need.

1135
00:40:49,510 --> 00:40:50,280
I—

1136
00:40:50,320 --> 00:40:51,840
I'm running a stall with a friend now.

1137
00:40:51,840 --> 00:40:53,100
We've made some money.

1138
00:40:53,440 --> 00:40:54,220
A friend?

1139
00:40:54,650 --> 00:40:55,920
Where is this friend from?

1140
00:40:55,920 --> 00:40:57,050
A friend in Beijing.

1141
00:40:57,760 --> 00:40:58,890
A friend in Beijing?

1142
00:41:00,340 --> 00:41:01,540
Do you know them well?

1143
00:41:01,780 --> 00:41:02,920
When you're away from home,

1144
00:41:02,920 --> 00:41:04,050
safety comes first.

1145
00:41:04,050 --> 00:41:06,050
You don't need to worry about money.

1146
00:41:06,230 --> 00:41:07,190
I'm all grown up now.

1147
00:41:07,190 --> 00:41:08,450
I can earn my own money.

1148
00:41:09,300 --> 00:41:09,920
My mom

1149
00:41:10,110 --> 00:41:12,420
makes beautiful clothes, and I sell them.

1150
00:41:12,420 --> 00:41:14,670
Like mother, like daughter.

1151
00:41:16,610 --> 00:41:17,210
By the way,

1152
00:41:17,710 --> 00:41:19,300
the girl I live with

1153
00:41:19,300 --> 00:41:20,940
keeps saying my clothes look great,

1154
00:41:20,940 --> 00:41:22,530
and that I've got good taste.

1155
00:41:22,530 --> 00:41:24,460
I told her it's all thanks to my mom.

1156
00:41:26,130 --> 00:41:27,190
Alright, alright.

1157
00:41:27,280 --> 00:41:28,600
I can't out-talk you.

1158
00:41:29,360 --> 00:41:31,020
But don't overwork yourself.

1159
00:41:31,050 --> 00:41:32,520
Take it easy, okay?

1160
00:41:32,730 --> 00:41:33,460
Don't worry.

1161
00:41:34,090 --> 00:41:35,690
Are you and Uncle doing well?

1162
00:41:36,380 --> 00:41:37,670
We're both fine.

1163
00:41:37,730 --> 00:41:38,930
Don't worry about us.

1164
00:41:40,940 --> 00:41:42,550
Alright, I have to go now.

1165
00:41:42,980 --> 00:41:44,110
Don't send me money.

1166
00:41:44,280 --> 00:41:45,480
Take care of yourself,

1167
00:41:45,480 --> 00:41:47,080
and send my regards to Uncle.

1168
00:41:47,150 --> 00:41:47,530
Also,

1169
00:41:47,800 --> 00:41:49,880
when will the home phone be installed?

1170
00:41:49,880 --> 00:41:51,860
Soon, we've already booked the technician.

1171
00:41:51,860 --> 00:41:53,110
He'll come install it in a few days.

1172
00:41:53,110 --> 00:41:54,630
It'll be more convenient then.

1173
00:41:54,630 --> 00:41:56,070
You can call home,

1174
00:41:56,070 --> 00:41:57,000
or call the shop.

1175
00:41:57,380 --> 00:41:58,860
If anything happens, tell us right away.

1176
00:41:58,860 --> 00:41:59,420
Got it?

1177
00:41:59,630 --> 00:42:00,820
Okay, got it, got it.

1178
00:42:01,190 --> 00:42:01,900
Make sure you eat well,

1179
00:42:01,900 --> 00:42:02,760
and take care of yourself.

1180
00:42:02,760 --> 00:42:03,440
Okay, okay, okay.

1181
00:42:03,440 --> 00:42:04,370
Go get busy then.

1182
00:42:09,090 --> 00:42:09,690
From home?

1183
00:42:10,260 --> 00:42:10,800
My mom.

1184
00:42:11,420 --> 00:42:13,350
You're really close with your mom.

1185
00:42:13,460 --> 00:42:14,480
She nags a lot too.

1186
00:42:15,590 --> 00:42:16,000
You...

1187
00:42:17,000 --> 00:42:17,930
I'm heading out.

1188
00:42:18,150 --> 00:42:19,410
I'm meeting Mr. Cui

1189
00:42:19,460 --> 00:42:20,920
to talk about meeting a director.

1190
00:42:20,920 --> 00:42:21,760
Then hurry up and go.

1191
00:42:21,760 --> 00:42:22,590
I'm off then.

1192
00:42:22,860 --> 00:42:23,510
Good luck.

1193
00:42:28,360 --> 00:42:29,020
Well,

1194
00:42:29,380 --> 00:42:30,820
besides the two thousand,

1195
00:42:30,820 --> 00:42:32,530
I'll wire her

1196
00:42:32,530 --> 00:42:33,460
the five hundred

1197
00:42:33,570 --> 00:42:34,900
from the shop register.

1198
00:42:35,800 --> 00:42:37,460
No need, she still has some.

1199
00:42:37,650 --> 00:42:38,650
Let's send the money

1200
00:42:38,650 --> 00:42:39,510
month by month.

1201
00:42:40,050 --> 00:42:41,820
If a girl carries too much money,

1202
00:42:41,820 --> 00:42:43,280
she might attract trouble.

1203
00:42:43,280 --> 00:42:44,590
Two thousand isn't enough.

1204
00:42:44,590 --> 00:42:47,320
She must be short on money
but too afraid to say so.

1205
00:42:47,500 --> 00:42:48,230
It's enough.

1206
00:42:48,400 --> 00:42:49,460
I've done the math.

1207
00:42:51,000 --> 00:42:53,800
I feel more at ease
when she has some extra money on hand.

1208
00:42:53,800 --> 00:42:55,260
I'm going to wire it to her.

1209
00:42:56,300 --> 00:42:56,670
You...
